$ Registry: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\VisualStudio\Setup

{ CachePath

  The → Windows/registry/tree-structure/value of `CachePath` specifies where package manifests and, optionally, payloads are stored.

  The default is → Windows/dirs/ProgramData/Microsoft/VisualStudio/Packages[`%ProgramData%\Microsoft\VisualStudio\Packages`]

}
{ SharedInstallationPath

  `SharedInstallationPath` specifies the directory where some packages across → Windows/development/Visual-Studio/versions[versions] are stored.

  The default location is → Windows/dirs/Program-Files-x86/Microsoft-Visual-Studio/Shared[`%ProgramFiles(x86)%\Microsoft Visual Studio\Shared`]


}

links:
